edu.ucsb.cs56.drawings.qwertyuiop5040.advanced

Class TriangularFlag

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucsb.cs56.drawings.utilities.GeneralPathWrapper
      • edu.ucsb.cs56.drawings.qwertyuiop5040.advanced.TriangularFlag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Shape
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PirateFlag

    public class TriangularFlag
extends GeneralPathWrapper
implements Shape
    A triangular flag with a flag pole that the user can specify the x,y as well as the width and height of the flag. The user can optionally specify the ratio of width and height between the flag pole and the flag itself. For example a ratio of 3 for flag pole height to the flag means the flag pole is 3 times as long as the flag itself.
    Version:
    for CS56, F16, UCSB
    Author:
    Hanqing Wang

        public TriangularFlag(double x,
                      double y,
                      double width,
                      double height,
                      double flagPoleWidthRatio,
                      double flagPoleHeightRatio)
        Constructor will draw a triangular flag consisting of a rectangle for the flag pole and two sloping lines for the triangle
        Parameters:
        x - x coord of top left corner of flag
        y - y coord of top left corner of flag
        width - of the flag (including the flag pole, if there is one)
        height - of flag (including the flag pole, if there is one)
        hasFlagPole - determines whether flag will be drawn with a flagpole
        flagPoleHeightRatio - ratio of the height of the flag pole to the height of the flag, cannot be negative
